WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:52.713 --> 00:01:55.308
All right. everybody out.

3
00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:02.852
I got to call this in.

4
00:02:03.357 --> 00:02:04.552
Miss?

5
00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:19.363
Dying on a streetcar
while dancing to <i>YMCA.</i>

6
00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:20.740
What do you think?

7
00:02:20.807 --> 00:02:22.673
Sounds like a crappy way to go.

8
00:02:22.876 --> 00:02:25.744
Hey. body I.D.'ed
as Serena Dunbrook.

9
00:02:25.946 --> 00:02:27.938
Thirty-four. lives in the Pearl.

10
00:02:28.015 --> 00:02:29.210
Probably on her way to work.

11
00:02:29.282 --> 00:02:32.252
Which is a swank law firm of
Berman. Rautbort and Associates.

12
00:02:32.319 --> 00:02:34.254
Wallet biopsy on her purse?

13
00:02:36.089 --> 00:02:37.648
So this is our victim?

14
00:02:38.358 --> 00:02:40.259
That's what she
used to look like.

15
00:03:02.215 --> 00:03:04.707
It's unofficial. but geek squad's
thinking anaphylactic shock.

16
00:03:04.785 --> 00:03:06.617
That could happen
from one little bee sting?

17
00:03:06.687 --> 00:03:08.398
We need to get the ME
on her medical records.

18
00:03:08.422 --> 00:03:09.822
see if she was
allergic to anything.

19
00:03:09.956 --> 00:03:11.652
Ask me. this is a
waste of your time.

20
00:03:12.025 --> 00:03:13.755
We don't know if this
was an accident yet.

21
00:03:13.927 --> 00:03:15.361
Must have been
a killer bee. huh?

22
00:03:15.429 --> 00:03:17.022
There was a swarm
that attacked a dog

23
00:03:17.097 --> 00:03:18.531
at Cathedral Park last week.

24
00:03:19.266 --> 00:03:21.462
Okay. come on. 20
bucks says no foul play.

25
00:03:21.968 --> 00:03:23.596
Who's in? Me.

26
00:03:24.337 --> 00:03:25.566
Pay up.

27
00:03:27.174 --> 00:03:29.405
It looks like a puncture wound.

28
00:03:31.478 --> 00:03:32.707
Maybe a needle.

29
00:03:32.913 --> 00:03:34.541
More like a nail.

30
00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:37.544
Time to get Harper out of bed.

31
00:03:37.617 --> 00:03:39.848
Ooh. lucky you.

32
00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:41.682
Bet your gal's wearing
something sexy.

33
00:03:42.923 --> 00:03:44.289
Here it is.

34
00:03:45.258 --> 00:03:47.557
Cause of death.
anaphylactic shock.

35
00:03:47.794 --> 00:03:49.319
Mode. apitoxin.

36
00:03:50.330 --> 00:03:51.457
As in bee venom.

37
00:03:51.531 --> 00:03:52.555
Gold star.

38
00:03:52.799 --> 00:03:55.234
<i>Phylum anthropoda.</i>
class <i>insecta.</i>

39
00:03:55.368 --> 00:03:57.064
I've sent a sample
to a local apiarist

40
00:03:57.137 --> 00:03:58.628
for further analysis.

41
00:03:58.705 --> 00:04:01.106
That's a beekeeper. I
can play this game. too.

42
00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:03.041
Now. let's pretend that
it wasn't a bee sting.

43
00:04:03.443 --> 00:04:05.071
Oh. going for the extra credit.

44
00:04:06.646 --> 00:04:08.410
Well. it's definitely
a puncture wound.

45
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:10.979
But I can't tell
you what made it.

46
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:15.347
Well. I've never seen
a needle gauge this big.

47
00:04:15.555 --> 00:04:17.251
So. was she
allergic to apitoxin?

48
00:04:17.390 --> 00:04:20.952
No. But medical records
never kept anyone from dying.

49
00:04:21.461 --> 00:04:25.193
I found close to 50 milligrams
of apitoxin in her system.

50
00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:29.197
A bee sting carries
about 0.1 milligram.

51
00:04:30.036 --> 00:04:32.437
That would make it a bee
the size of LeBron James.

52
00:04:32.539 --> 00:04:34.030
More like the Big
Three combined.

53
00:04:34.174 --> 00:04:35.369
Okay. sports fans.

54
00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:37.911
so Serena Dunbrook gets
on a Portland streetcar.

55
00:04:37.978 --> 00:04:39.776
people erupt into
spontaneous dance...

56
00:04:39.846 --> 00:04:42.127
And our opportunistic killer
takes advantage of the chaos.

57
00:04:42.182 --> 00:04:43.480
and injects her with bee venom.

58
00:04:43.617 --> 00:04:44.778
Weird. but possible.

59
00:04:44.885 --> 00:04:46.513
And definitely.

60
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:48.154
definitely a homicide.

61
00:04:54.594 --> 00:04:56.825
7:14 a.m.. there's your victim.

62
00:04:57.097 --> 00:04:59.157
Got her. Move past this.

63
00:05:00.267 --> 00:05:04.568
All right. anything? Anyone eyeing
her wrong? Reaching for anything?

64
00:05:06.039 --> 00:05:07.371
Okay. now slow it back down.

65
00:05:10.177 --> 00:05:11.817
That looks like they're
waiting for a cue.

66
00:05:14.047 --> 00:05:15.777
Now that's a flash mob.

67
00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:20.730
There. We've lost her.
Can you do anything. Wu?

68
00:05:20.754 --> 00:05:22.382
No. that's it. The
camera's stationary.

69
00:05:22.455 --> 00:05:23.821
She falls out of sight.

70
00:05:24.624 --> 00:05:27.059
That flash mob was
our witness pool.

71
00:05:27.127 --> 00:05:28.254
Get this on the news.

72
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.194
Anyone innocent should
come right forward.

73
00:05:30.263 --> 00:05:32.542
I want your full attention on
the streetcar death. all right?

74
00:05:32.566 --> 00:05:34.677
We don't need the city scared
to use public transportation.

75
00:05:34.701 --> 00:05:36.245
Now. Harrison Berman.
the head of the vic's law firm.

76
00:05:36.269 --> 00:05:37.430
he's upset. he's angry.

77
00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:38.984
We're going to
have to deal with this.

78
00:05:39.306 --> 00:05:40.786
You sure this wasn't
a random killing?

79
00:05:40.874 --> 00:05:41.967
Doesn't look like it.

80
00:05:42.108 --> 00:05:44.148
All right. well. anything
you need. you let me know.

81
00:05:46.813 --> 00:05:49.078
<i>Everybody just loved Serena.</i>

82
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:52.111
You couldn't meet that girl
and not fall for her charms.

83
00:05:52.319 --> 00:05:54.015
Top of her class at law school.

84
00:05:54.287 --> 00:05:57.451
I was a year beneath her. She
kind of took me under her wing.

85
00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:58.668
And was Serena
working on anything

86
00:05:58.692 --> 00:05:59.932
that could have motivated this?

87
00:06:00.093 --> 00:06:01.186
A particular case?

88
00:06:01.494 --> 00:06:02.894
A problematic client? Anything?

89
00:06:02.963 --> 00:06:04.522
Not that I remember.

90
00:06:04.664 --> 00:06:06.360
Not everyone likes lawyers.

91
00:06:06.733 --> 00:06:09.813
Well. we'll need to look through all of
Serena's case work just to be certain.

92
00:06:10.403 --> 00:06:11.803
Full access.

93
00:06:11.872 --> 00:06:13.534
Whatever you need.

94
00:06:14.341 --> 00:06:16.242
I'll messenger everything over.

95
00:06:16.443 --> 00:06:18.378
Now. what about
her personal life?

96
00:06:18.845 --> 00:06:20.609
Boyfriend? Fiancé?

97
00:06:21.114 --> 00:06:23.140
I mean. she wasn't
ready to settle down.

98
00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:24.309
She was...

99
00:06:26.253 --> 00:06:30.054
I mean. she was really
happy with who she was.

100
00:06:31.691 --> 00:06:33.091
I'm sorry.

101
00:06:34.761 --> 00:06:35.854
Thanks.

102
00:06:36.062 --> 00:06:38.327
You just find the
animal who did this.

103
00:06:38.498 --> 00:06:39.966
We'll do everything we can. sir.

104
00:06:42.269 --> 00:06:43.669
I'm sorry for your loss.

105
00:06:45.138 --> 00:06:47.733
Harper's bee man just buzzed me.

106
00:06:48.842 --> 00:06:50.435
Yeah. I went there.

107
00:06:53.613 --> 00:06:55.206
What makes a guy
want to work everyday

108
00:06:55.282 --> 00:06:56.910
in such a dangerous environment?

109
00:06:56.983 --> 00:06:59.077
Robbery homicide
too tame for you?

110
00:07:02.188 --> 00:07:03.679
The queen.

111
00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:05.817
She likes you. Detective.

112
00:07:07.327 --> 00:07:08.420
Don't be fooled.

113
00:07:08.495 --> 00:07:10.020
She's fiercely
protective of her hive.

114
00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:12.622
It's unusual that she
should show herself like this.

115
00:07:13.233 --> 00:07:15.395
So. Mr. Spinella... Professor.

116
00:07:16.403 --> 00:07:17.996
Professor Spinella.

117
00:07:18.071 --> 00:07:20.583
were you able to analyze the
apitoxin that our coroner sent over?

118
00:07:20.607 --> 00:07:23.236
Indeed. I did. Detective.

119
00:07:24.044 --> 00:07:25.171
And?

120
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:27.478
Well. it's not synthetic.

121
00:07:28.081 --> 00:07:31.779
You mean. someone harvested 50
milligrams of apitoxin from actual bees?

122
00:07:32.085 --> 00:07:33.178
Apparently so.

123
00:07:33.320 --> 00:07:35.118
You see. natural
apitoxin carries

124
00:07:35.221 --> 00:07:37.383
geographical traits.
uh. signatures.

125
00:07:37.590 --> 00:07:39.991
Via analysis of the
chemical ratios of the venom.

126
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:42.052
one can determine
the geo-regional origins.

127
00:07:42.762 --> 00:07:45.527
So. where did the apitoxin that
killed Serena Dunbrook come from?

128
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:48.598
Well. I'd definitely
categorize it as exotic.

129
00:07:48.668 --> 00:07:50.830
which would normally mean China.

130
00:07:50.904 --> 00:07:52.566
Africa and France.

131
00:07:53.406 --> 00:07:56.774
However. your apitoxin shows
levels of phospholipase A2

132
00:07:56.843 --> 00:07:58.334
that I've never seen before.

133
00:07:59.179 --> 00:08:01.580
This apitoxin has
no known origin.

134
00:08:03.550 --> 00:08:04.550
Excuse me.

135
00:08:06.252 --> 00:08:07.276
Unknown origin?

136
00:08:07.354 --> 00:08:08.652
What is this? Sci-fi crap?

137
00:08:08.722 --> 00:08:10.466
That stuff couldn't just
come out of nowhere.

138
00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:11.734
You think he's hiding something?

139
00:08:11.758 --> 00:08:12.758
Detectives!

140
00:08:13.893 --> 00:08:16.362
In case I'm on
that list of yours.

141
00:08:16.696 --> 00:08:19.461
harvesting apitoxin in
that amount would require

142
00:08:19.532 --> 00:08:22.468
much more sophisticated
equipment than I have at my disposal.

143
00:08:22.869 --> 00:08:24.201
Besides I was at

144
00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:25.614
the Howard Johnson
in Eugene last night

145
00:08:25.638 --> 00:08:28.870
for this year's Oregon
Beekeepers'-Con.

146
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:31.971
Pretty crowded convention?

147
00:08:32.245 --> 00:08:34.578
Well. there's 12
of us. actually.

148
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:36.325
Anything else I
can help you with?

149
00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:37.442
No. Professor.

150
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:38.541
We'll be in touch.

151
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:43.914
A streetcar full of dancers

152
00:08:43.990 --> 00:08:45.822
and 12 bee geeks
in a motel room.

153
00:08:45.892 --> 00:08:48.157
Your suspect pool's
getting bigger. huh?

154
00:08:48.661 --> 00:08:50.220
<i>TV coverage paid off.</i>

155
00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:52.799
Say hi to your flash mob.

156
00:08:52.866 --> 00:08:54.061
Excuse me.

157
00:08:54.134 --> 00:08:55.796
Twenty-two. so far.

158
00:08:55.969 --> 00:08:57.232
By the way.

159
00:08:57.303 --> 00:08:59.772
Captain's been taking a
keen interest in this one.

160
00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:01.307
He's even asking
me what's going on.

161
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.442
Listen. then do us a favor.

162
00:09:03.510 --> 00:09:05.445
while we talk to
the Village People.

163
00:09:05.578 --> 00:09:06.658
can you check out the alibi

164
00:09:06.713 --> 00:09:08.113
for Professor
Spinella last night?

165
00:09:08.681 --> 00:09:11.116
Some convention at
the Ho-Jo's in Eugene.

166
00:09:11.184 --> 00:09:13.949
And get us the name of every
beekeeper who was there.

167
00:09:15.055 --> 00:09:16.421
No problem.

168
00:09:17.824 --> 00:09:19.918
Have fun with
your interrogations.

169
00:09:19.993 --> 00:09:21.222
We will.

170
00:09:22.395 --> 00:09:24.261
I didn't know anyone...
On that street car.

171
00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:25.992
Every one of them
was a... Stranger.

172
00:09:26.266 --> 00:09:28.258
Then why were you
there? I got the invite.

173
00:09:28.435 --> 00:09:29.435
Totally random.

174
00:09:29.502 --> 00:09:30.862
Tweet telling me
a... Time and a...

175
00:09:30.904 --> 00:09:32.236
Place and what to do.

176
00:09:32.338 --> 00:09:33.704
I get on at... Yamhill.

177
00:09:33.840 --> 00:09:35.706
And dance to <i>YMCA.</i>

178
00:09:37.110 --> 00:09:38.134
We've been told.

179
00:09:38.278 --> 00:09:40.338
Yeah. and then. immediately...

180
00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:41.639
Get off at Alder.

181
00:09:41.714 --> 00:09:43.046
I didn't see that girl.

182
00:09:43.149 --> 00:09:44.393
There were a lot of us on there.

183
00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:45.942
We were just
dancing. having fun.

184
00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:47.530
How was I supposed
to... Know someone was...

185
00:09:47.554 --> 00:09:48.578
Getting killed?

186
00:09:51.991 --> 00:09:53.960
Can I go now?
Actually. no. Doug.

187
00:09:54.027 --> 00:09:55.290
I'd like to go over it again.

188
00:09:55.361 --> 00:09:57.296
if you don't mind.
From the beginning?

189
00:09:58.364 --> 00:10:00.404
Well. yeah. unless you
know what happens in the end.

190
00:10:03.103 --> 00:10:05.197
Like I said.

191
00:10:05.972 --> 00:10:08.203
I got the same invitation
as everybody else did.

192
00:10:08.475 --> 00:10:10.706
I figured I'd go have some
fun with some strangers.

193
00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:13.222
It just sounds like there's an
echo in here because I keep hearing

194
00:10:13.246 --> 00:10:15.238
the same thing
over and over again.

195
00:10:15.315 --> 00:10:17.216
Okay. can I see the tweet?

196
00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:19.082
Tech savvy guy like yourself.

197
00:10:19.185 --> 00:10:21.065
I'm sure you still have
it on your phone. right?

198
00:10:22.422 --> 00:10:23.617
Um...

199
00:10:24.491 --> 00:10:27.017
I got some personal
stuff on there.

200
00:10:30.163 --> 00:10:31.495
All right.

201
00:10:32.098 --> 00:10:33.691
Well. let's talk
about the victim.

202
00:10:34.167 --> 00:10:35.711
So. Serena Dunbrook
got on the streetcar

203
00:10:35.735 --> 00:10:36.998
around the time as you. right?

204
00:10:37.070 --> 00:10:38.129
She's a pretty girl.

205
00:10:38.338 --> 00:10:40.034
she stood right behind you.

206
00:10:40.707 --> 00:10:42.869
You know. did you
smell her perfume?

207
00:10:42.942 --> 00:10:45.605
Did it turn you on to be
rubbed up against her?

208
00:10:45.778 --> 00:10:46.802
No.

209
00:10:46.913 --> 00:10:49.348
Come on. Doug. we
have you on video.

210
00:10:49.415 --> 00:10:51.543
I was on the other side. Really?

211
00:10:52.352 --> 00:10:53.696
Because in your
previous statement.

212
00:10:53.720 --> 00:10:55.880
you said you didn't see
her at all. so which one is it?

213
00:10:58.091 --> 00:11:00.219
All right. let me see
the phone. Doug.

214
00:11:00.293 --> 00:11:01.533
unless you're hiding something.

215
00:11:23.049 --> 00:11:26.713
A.G. waiver turned up a dummy
account opened with a spam email.

216
00:11:26.886 --> 00:11:28.787
All it takes is half
a brain and a laptop

217
00:11:28.888 --> 00:11:30.550
to manipulate an IP address.

218
00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:32.859
The benefit of social media.

219
00:11:32.926 --> 00:11:35.122
anyone can arrange
cover for a murder.

220
00:11:37.830 --> 00:11:40.322
You get something off
this Doug Shellow guy?

221
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:46.032
Yeah.

222
00:11:46.506 --> 00:11:48.099
I think I just did.

223
00:12:00.987 --> 00:12:03.456
Abandoned paper mill?
This doesn't look like home.

224
00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:15.964
Know anything about
Primrose Paper?

225
00:12:16.035 --> 00:12:17.560
I've heard of it. That's all.

226
00:12:17.637 --> 00:12:19.697
Old family business.
been here forever.

227
00:12:19.772 --> 00:12:20.883
Do you really think Doug Shellow

228
00:12:20.907 --> 00:12:22.117
and John Coleman
know each other?

229
00:12:22.141 --> 00:12:23.871
Let's hope letting
them go pays off.

230
00:12:45.198 --> 00:12:47.224
Hello. conspiracy.

231
00:12:48.468 --> 00:12:50.699
So much for everybody
claiming to be strangers.

232
00:12:55.742 --> 00:12:57.040
Who is that?

233
00:12:57.810 --> 00:12:59.472
I can't get a good look at her.

234
00:13:12.191 --> 00:13:13.489
Ah! Run!

235
00:13:17.063 --> 00:13:18.827
Ah! Ah!

236
00:13:20.266 --> 00:13:21.393
Ah!

237
00:13:25.171 --> 00:13:26.901
Get in this office!

238
00:13:28.875 --> 00:13:29.934
Ah!

239
00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:37.310
What the hell is going on?

240
00:13:37.383 --> 00:13:38.663
Where'd all these
bees come from?

241
00:13:38.718 --> 00:13:39.718
I don't know!

242
00:13:39.786 --> 00:13:41.812
Keep them out! Here.
use some of these! Here!

243
00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:52.856
I've never seen so many
damn bees in my life!

244
00:13:59.472 --> 00:14:01.703
Wait. where'd they go?

245
00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:05.702
Maybe they're
hiding. waiting for us.

246
00:14:06.479 --> 00:14:08.141
I don't think bees hide.

247
00:14:16.489 --> 00:14:19.323
Oh. man. I got at least a
couple dozen bee stings.

248
00:14:22.161 --> 00:14:23.424
This is crazy.

249
00:14:23.496 --> 00:14:25.021
Someone gets
killed with bee venom

250
00:14:25.098 --> 00:14:26.430
and we get attacked by a swarm?

251
00:14:26.499 --> 00:14:27.865
I don't think it's
a coincidence.

252
00:14:27.934 --> 00:14:30.927
You know. maybe Wu was
right about a giant killer bee.

253
00:14:33.139 --> 00:14:35.506
Come on. Let's
get you some help.

254
00:14:38.177 --> 00:14:39.201
Ow!

255
00:14:39.278 --> 00:14:41.213
You're a bigger baby than he is.

256
00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:42.942
Two beers. One water.

257
00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:45.456
Bees usually sting when
threatened or provoked.

258
00:14:45.485 --> 00:14:46.729
Did you kick a
hive or something?

259
00:14:46.753 --> 00:14:48.030
No. they just came
out of nowhere.

260
00:14:48.054 --> 00:14:49.522
headed straight for yours truly.

261
00:14:49.622 --> 00:14:51.614
Aw. maybe you were their flower.

262
00:14:51.958 --> 00:14:52.958
Excuse me?

263
00:14:53.159 --> 00:14:54.719
Bees are highly
effective communicators.

264
00:14:54.994 --> 00:14:57.272
A scout will fly around until
they find the perfect flower.

265
00:14:57.296 --> 00:14:58.559
then it goes back to the hive

266
00:14:58.631 --> 00:15:00.293
and signals the
others to follow.

267
00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:01.993
You learned all
that in vet school?

268
00:15:02.101 --> 00:15:03.729
Nope. Animal Planet.

269
00:15:03.836 --> 00:15:06.305
Well. they say anything about
training bees to attack people?

270
00:15:06.606 --> 00:15:08.666
That sounds more
like a bad movie.

271
00:15:08.741 --> 00:15:10.801
Shellow and Coleman
are still our best leads.

272
00:15:10.877 --> 00:15:12.277
I just put out an APB.

273
00:15:12.345 --> 00:15:13.574
What about our mystery woman?

274
00:15:14.046 --> 00:15:16.277
The two guys were
reporting to her.

275
00:15:16.349 --> 00:15:18.394
So. there's got to be a connection
between the three of them.

276
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:20.614
the mill and Serena Dunbrook.

277
00:15:20.953 --> 00:15:24.117
Let's take a look at the
case files Berman sent us.

278
00:15:25.124 --> 00:15:26.124
Uh-uh.

279
00:15:26.192 --> 00:15:27.436
My patient is not
doing anything.

280
00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:30.828
but resting and not scratching
for the next eight hours.

281
00:15:30.897 --> 00:15:33.275
Dude. if you were a dog. I would
have already tranquilized you.

282
00:15:33.299 --> 00:15:34.299
No. she's right.

283
00:15:34.467 --> 00:15:35.867
I got this. You go to sleep.

284
00:15:36.269 --> 00:15:38.067
Thanks. Doc. Bye.

285
00:15:41.808 --> 00:15:44.869
I know. you're sorry.
but you have to work.

286
00:15:45.678 --> 00:15:48.978
I just thought I'd let you
know what you'll be missing.

287
00:15:56.289 --> 00:15:58.121
I just have to do some research.

288
00:15:58.191 --> 00:15:59.191
Won't be long.

289
00:15:59.659 --> 00:16:01.821
Yeah. it will. You've been
turning this no sleep thing

290
00:16:01.894 --> 00:16:03.624
into an art form lately.

291
00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:05.560
Goodnight.

292
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:12.897
"A Hexenbiest mark can
be found under the tongue

293
00:17:12.965 --> 00:17:15.457
"in both human form
and morphed form."

294
00:17:32.618 --> 00:17:34.086
Hey. it's me.

295
00:17:35.154 --> 00:17:37.919
Did you hear about that girl
who was murdered on the tram?

296
00:17:44.964 --> 00:17:47.160
Whoa! Easy there. 5-0!

297
00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:49.969
You called me. remember?

298
00:17:52.705 --> 00:17:55.197
Man. don't you have
a partner for this stuff?

299
00:17:55.274 --> 00:17:57.853
Yeah. sure. because if I told him my
two main suspects turned into bees.

300
00:17:57.877 --> 00:17:59.038
he'd completely understand.

301
00:17:59.111 --> 00:18:00.272
Lucky me.

302
00:18:01.948 --> 00:18:03.314
So. Mellifers. huh?

303
00:18:03.382 --> 00:18:04.626
Yeah. they had something
to do with a murder

304
00:18:04.650 --> 00:18:06.243
on a Portland streetcar. Murder?

305
00:18:06.485 --> 00:18:07.919
Not really their shtick.

306
00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:09.147
Bees bite. don't they?

307
00:18:09.221 --> 00:18:10.917
Yeah. but only when...
Threatened. I know.

308
00:18:10.990 --> 00:18:13.468
But I read in the book that they
also have something to do with

309
00:18:13.492 --> 00:18:15.188
balancing the ecotone.

310
00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:16.320
What does that mean?

311
00:18:16.395 --> 00:18:18.261
That's just some fancy
pants mumbo jumbo

312
00:18:18.331 --> 00:18:20.027
for saying they're like
gossips. you know?

313
00:18:20.232 --> 00:18:22.531
The creature
community switchboard.

314
00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:24.293
Or social media?

315
00:18:25.905 --> 00:18:28.033
And if a Mellifer
sends out a message.

316
00:18:28.107 --> 00:18:30.508
it definitely means something
sketchy is going on somewhere.

317
00:18:30.776 --> 00:18:33.507
Well. Hank and I were attacked
by a swarm of bees earlier.

318
00:18:33.579 --> 00:18:35.070
if that's sketchy
enough for you.

319
00:18:39.852 --> 00:18:42.481
We were following two guys
who turned out to be Mellifers.

320
00:18:42.955 --> 00:18:44.583
and they met a woman.

321
00:18:46.425 --> 00:18:48.417
Yeah. And?

322
00:18:49.095 --> 00:18:51.860
What. you think I know everything
about every creature out there?

323
00:18:51.998 --> 00:18:53.358
I don't need you
for what you know.

324
00:18:53.399 --> 00:18:54.492
I need your nose.

325
00:18:54.767 --> 00:18:55.928
Oh. I get it.

326
00:18:56.002 --> 00:18:57.630
So. little Timmy's
stuck in a well.

327
00:18:57.703 --> 00:18:59.296
and you need Lassie
to come find him?

328
00:18:59.505 --> 00:19:01.770
Boy. you really know how
to butter a guy up for a favor.

329
00:19:01.841 --> 00:19:03.742
I got a bottle of '78
Bordeaux in my trunk.

330
00:19:04.043 --> 00:19:05.602
I can maybe catch a scent.

331
00:19:05.678 --> 00:19:06.805
Okay.

332
00:19:07.613 --> 00:19:09.707
Now. you said Mellifers
deliver messages.

333
00:19:10.850 --> 00:19:13.290
What kind of message is it when
they murder an innocent woman?

334
00:19:13.819 --> 00:19:15.617
Maybe she wasn't so innocent.

335
00:19:25.231 --> 00:19:27.757
Mellifers only have
one natural enemy.

336
00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:28.833
Hexenbiests.

337
00:19:29.001 --> 00:19:30.629
Look at you. hitting the books.

338
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:36.836
Oh. yeah.

339
00:19:36.909 --> 00:19:39.469
I'm definitely getting
a female scent here.

340
00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:42.246
Undeniable.

341
00:19:42.748 --> 00:19:44.148
You're that sure?

342
00:19:44.917 --> 00:19:47.512
No. her perfume.
it's called Undeniable.

343
00:19:50.089 --> 00:19:51.113
Hey. wait up.

344
00:19:51.257 --> 00:19:52.885
Don't you dare say "heel."

345
00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:57.227
They didn't come in here.
We saw them leave the mill.

346
00:19:57.296 --> 00:19:59.527
Hey. the nose knows.

347
00:20:02.568 --> 00:20:05.094
I'm getting a big time
whiff of her in here.

348
00:20:09.275 --> 00:20:11.335
Maybe she left something behind.

349
00:20:15.781 --> 00:20:17.875
Oh. yeah. Scent's real strong.

350
00:20:22.755 --> 00:20:25.281
She could come
back at some point.

351
00:20:27.093 --> 00:20:30.257
Maybe we could crack
that Bordeaux while we wait.

352
00:20:30.463 --> 00:20:31.931
Her name's Melissa Wincroft.

353
00:20:33.132 --> 00:20:34.293
Whoa.

354
00:20:34.967 --> 00:20:38.028
Did you just. like. Grimm that
in some kind of telepathic way?

355
00:20:38.337 --> 00:20:40.738
No. I read it off an envelope.

356
00:20:41.173 --> 00:20:43.267
Melissa Wincroft. owner and CEO.

357
00:20:43.676 --> 00:20:44.820
This must have been her office.

358
00:20:44.844 --> 00:20:45.903
That's cheating.

359
00:20:48.147 --> 00:20:50.013
Well. I sniffed her out.

360
00:20:50.382 --> 00:20:51.509
Good boy.

361
00:21:00.159 --> 00:21:02.594
Yeah. this is
definitely her place.

362
00:21:32.525 --> 00:21:34.436
This is so the part
in the horror movie

363
00:21:34.460 --> 00:21:36.395
where the sidekick gets it.

364
00:21:36.462 --> 00:21:37.691
Just stay close.

365
00:21:59.084 --> 00:22:00.143
What is that?

366
00:22:16.969 --> 00:22:19.063
Tell me we are
not going upstairs.

367
00:22:21.473 --> 00:22:23.271
We're going upstairs?

368
00:23:14.493 --> 00:23:15.586
Damn.

369
00:23:16.662 --> 00:23:18.153
I know. right?

370
00:23:18.297 --> 00:23:20.289
Forensics says this stuff
is a preliminary match

371
00:23:20.366 --> 00:23:22.232
to the apitoxin in
Serena's system.

372
00:23:22.301 --> 00:23:23.530
That clears our beekeepers.

373
00:23:23.602 --> 00:23:25.400
Which makes Melissa
Wincroft our primary

374
00:23:25.471 --> 00:23:27.133
if we could find her.

375
00:23:27.573 --> 00:23:29.474
She didn't sell this
place or buy a new one.

376
00:23:29.575 --> 00:23:32.272
It's like she just picked
up and disappeared.

377
00:23:32.778 --> 00:23:36.078
Now. can you tell me how in the hell
you found this woman and her hive?

378
00:23:36.482 --> 00:23:38.451
Well. it's all in
the legal files.

379
00:23:38.517 --> 00:23:40.042
I read them last night.

380
00:23:40.119 --> 00:23:41.178
Everything's connected.

381
00:23:41.720 --> 00:23:44.189
Shellow. Coleman.
the mill. even Serena.

382
00:23:44.256 --> 00:23:45.622
You could have called me.

383
00:23:46.025 --> 00:23:47.926
Hey. Doctor told you to rest.

384
00:23:47.993 --> 00:23:49.291
Eh. fine.

385
00:23:50.796 --> 00:23:53.265
All right. So. connect the dots.

386
00:23:53.832 --> 00:23:56.392
Well. messy class action
lawsuit about a year ago.

387
00:23:56.468 --> 00:23:57.902
Serena represented Ameri-mill

388
00:23:57.970 --> 00:23:59.530
in a hostile takeover
of Primrose Paper.

389
00:24:00.039 --> 00:24:02.167
The employees tried
to fight it. they lost.

390
00:24:02.241 --> 00:24:03.709
Let me guess. two
of those employees

391
00:24:03.776 --> 00:24:05.244
were Doug Shellow
and John Coleman.

392
00:24:05.377 --> 00:24:07.869
Exactly. Melissa
Wincroft was their boss.

393
00:24:07.947 --> 00:24:10.158
Her family owned and operated
the mill for over a century.

394
00:24:10.182 --> 00:24:11.182
She had the most to lose.

395
00:24:11.250 --> 00:24:12.827
So she's taking revenge
on Serena for getting

396
00:24:12.851 --> 00:24:14.581
her company shut down. Mmm-hmm.

397
00:24:14.653 --> 00:24:15.848
Detectives.

398
00:24:15.921 --> 00:24:17.685
Sergeant Wu just called
from Chapman Square.

399
00:24:17.756 --> 00:24:19.725
There's been another
flash mob murder.

400
00:24:28.901 --> 00:24:30.995
<i>Another tweet.
another flash mob.</i>

401
00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:33.369
This time. death by <i>Hokey Pokey.</i>

402
00:24:33.439 --> 00:24:36.184
Witnesses say the victim was doing
her morning yoga routine when it started.

403
00:24:36.208 --> 00:24:37.904
Eye in the sky caught it all.

404
00:24:37.977 --> 00:24:39.054
Shellow or Coleman in the group?

405
00:24:39.078 --> 00:24:41.206
Nope. Whole new set of
flash mobbers this time.

406
00:24:41.313 --> 00:24:43.325
But unis grabbed Shellow
and Coleman about an hour ago.

407
00:24:43.349 --> 00:24:44.408
They're at the precinct.

408
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:46.816
Both are staying silent
until they lawyer up.

409
00:24:50.622 --> 00:24:52.352
Tell me you got a
solid lead on this.

410
00:24:52.591 --> 00:24:55.527
We're zeroing in on a
suspect. Melissa Wincroft.

411
00:24:55.594 --> 00:24:56.789
That's Camilla Gotleib.

412
00:24:57.663 --> 00:24:59.655
She was on the Primrose
Paper case with Serena.

413
00:25:00.366 --> 00:25:01.925
Two dead lawyers
from the same firm.

414
00:25:02.001 --> 00:25:03.361
I'd say we got
ourselves a pattern.

415
00:25:03.435 --> 00:25:04.779
There's a third
lawyer on the case.

416
00:25:04.803 --> 00:25:06.362
I read it in the files.

417
00:25:07.039 --> 00:25:08.200
This is Detective Burkhardt.

418
00:25:08.273 --> 00:25:10.265
send a unit to Berman.
Rautbort and Associates.

419
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.573
and take an attorney
into protective custody.

420
00:25:12.644 --> 00:25:13.942
Her name is Adalind Schade.

421
00:25:17.783 --> 00:25:19.251
Miss Schade.

422
00:25:23.622 --> 00:25:24.622
You.

423
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:31.508
I'm Captain Renard. These are
detectives Griffin and Burkhardt.

424
00:25:31.797 --> 00:25:33.663
Detectives. thank you.

425
00:25:34.099 --> 00:25:35.176
You can thank
Detective Burkhardt.

426
00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:36.600
He's the one who
figured it all out.

427
00:25:37.369 --> 00:25:39.634
Actually. I'm still trying
to piece it all together.

428
00:25:40.672 --> 00:25:43.141
We need to ask you a few
questions if you're up for it.

429
00:25:43.208 --> 00:25:44.608
Can I offer you a cup of coffee?

430
00:25:45.310 --> 00:25:46.505
Thanks.

431
00:25:53.185 --> 00:25:54.619
Hey. Nick.

432
00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:56.220
Nick.

433
00:25:59.091 --> 00:26:00.218
You all right?

434
00:26:00.292 --> 00:26:02.591
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

435
00:26:04.530 --> 00:26:05.623
You know this woman?

436
00:26:07.199 --> 00:26:09.725
For a second. I thought I'd
seen her somewhere before.

437
00:26:10.069 --> 00:26:11.332
But you're not sure?

438
00:26:15.641 --> 00:26:17.109
There's a killer
out there that's

439
00:26:17.176 --> 00:26:19.168
already hit two
of her co-workers.

440
00:26:19.845 --> 00:26:22.178
If you know something
about Adalind Schade.

441
00:26:23.182 --> 00:26:24.616
now's the time to share it.

442
00:26:25.617 --> 00:26:27.779
I don't know anything
more about her than you do.

443
00:26:34.426 --> 00:26:37.954
Well. then just stay on your
game and keep her safe.

444
00:26:40.199 --> 00:26:41.827
Don't want her to
be number three.

445
00:26:47.272 --> 00:26:48.501
I need to see their tongues.

446
00:26:48.974 --> 00:26:50.340
Whatever floats your boat.

447
00:26:51.343 --> 00:26:53.778
Bodies were so swollen
I had to cut them out

448
00:26:53.846 --> 00:26:55.508
just to get a look inside.

449
00:26:55.581 --> 00:26:57.072
Here they are.

450
00:27:06.592 --> 00:27:09.084
Is there anything
strange on either of them?

451
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:10.656
Hmm.

452
00:27:11.697 --> 00:27:13.529
That? What made that mark?

453
00:27:13.866 --> 00:27:15.732
I thought that was weird. too.

454
00:27:15.801 --> 00:27:16.860
Here.

455
00:27:21.673 --> 00:27:23.437
But they're not tattoos.

456
00:27:23.509 --> 00:27:26.809
These marks have nothing
to do with their deaths.

457
00:27:27.646 --> 00:27:30.013
Who would do this
hideous thing to these girls?

458
00:27:32.384 --> 00:27:34.229
<i>Miss Wincroft. please
answer the question</i>

459
00:27:34.253 --> 00:27:36.279
<i>regarding the
quarterly earnings.</i>

460
00:27:36.355 --> 00:27:38.483
<i>This is not about the money.</i>

461
00:27:39.458 --> 00:27:41.689
<i>They are trying
to get rid of us.</i>

462
00:27:42.127 --> 00:27:45.063
<i>These workers.
everyone. we are a family.</i>

463
00:27:45.130 --> 00:27:47.759
<i>and they're trying to shut us
down to get us out of the way.</i>

464
00:27:47.900 --> 00:27:49.700
<i>The quarterly
earnings. Miss Wincroft.</i>

465
00:27:52.137 --> 00:27:54.003
<i>I know who's behind this.</i>

466
00:27:56.542 --> 00:27:58.773
<i>And they're not going
to get away with it.</i>

467
00:28:01.113 --> 00:28:03.082
Sounds like a threat to me.

468
00:28:03.282 --> 00:28:06.514
I can't believe she could have
done this to Serena and Camilla.

469
00:28:06.818 --> 00:28:09.014
We just don't want
you to be next.

470
00:28:09.121 --> 00:28:10.487
Now. Miss Schade...

471
00:28:10.756 --> 00:28:11.815
Please call me Adalind.

472
00:28:11.990 --> 00:28:13.185
All my friends do.

473
00:28:13.358 --> 00:28:14.917
All your friends are dead.

474
00:28:16.562 --> 00:28:18.463
I mean. it just
seems more personal

475
00:28:18.530 --> 00:28:19.964
than a business
transaction to me.

476
00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:21.557
Eye for an eye sort of thing.

477
00:28:21.633 --> 00:28:23.513
Like you hurt someone
close to her or something.

478
00:28:25.571 --> 00:28:28.040
Some people don't
get the big picture.

479
00:28:28.273 --> 00:28:29.332
I was just doing my job.

480
00:28:29.408 --> 00:28:30.671
Hey. so am I.

481
00:28:30.943 --> 00:28:32.434
Just trying to get
to the truth here.

482
00:28:32.811 --> 00:28:34.575
Unless Miss Schade
has something to hide.

483
00:28:35.981 --> 00:28:38.109
No more than you do. Detective.

484
00:28:40.619 --> 00:28:41.712
Look.

485
00:28:41.787 --> 00:28:44.279
I wish I could tell you something
more about Melissa Wincroft.

486
00:28:44.356 --> 00:28:46.188
but I really didn't know her.

487
00:28:46.658 --> 00:28:48.991
I told you. it wasn't personal.

488
00:28:49.695 --> 00:28:51.027
Yeah. well. maybe not for you.

489
00:28:51.964 --> 00:28:54.456
But if someone tried to take
something important away from me.

490
00:28:54.633 --> 00:28:56.659
I'd take it very personally.

491
00:28:56.868 --> 00:28:58.336
You know. let's take a break.

492
00:28:59.071 --> 00:29:00.266
Excuse us. Adalind.

493
00:29:03.408 --> 00:29:04.569
You coming?

494
00:29:10.616 --> 00:29:12.760
What's up with you? You're
treating her like she's the perp.

495
00:29:12.784 --> 00:29:14.162
I don't trust her.
You don't have to.

496
00:29:14.186 --> 00:29:15.484
You just have to protect her.

497
00:29:15.554 --> 00:29:17.682
Come on. We got to track
down Melissa Wincroft.

498
00:29:23.061 --> 00:29:24.495
Burkhardt remembers me.

499
00:29:24.663 --> 00:29:26.655
I pushed him. but he's
keeping it to himself.

500
00:29:26.832 --> 00:29:29.267
Maybe he's just
waiting to get me alone.

501
00:29:29.468 --> 00:29:31.027
I told you.

502
00:29:31.103 --> 00:29:32.901
I won't let anything
happen to you.

503
00:29:33.639 --> 00:29:35.733
Is that what you told
Serena and Camilla?

504
00:29:37.109 --> 00:29:39.271
Serena and Camilla are not you.

505
00:29:40.379 --> 00:29:42.075
I can take care of myself.

506
00:29:42.147 --> 00:29:44.241
Just find this Queen.

507
00:29:45.017 --> 00:29:47.179
or I'm not the only one
who's going to get stung.

508
00:29:53.258 --> 00:29:54.783
Got it. Thanks.

509
00:29:55.093 --> 00:29:57.153
No credit card
activity. no travel.

510
00:29:57.229 --> 00:29:59.095
no sign of Melissa
Wincroft in the system.

511
00:29:59.164 --> 00:30:01.258
She's got no known
family. Friends?

512
00:30:01.333 --> 00:30:03.244
Well. we know about John
Coleman and Doug Shellow.

513
00:30:03.268 --> 00:30:04.948
but I doubt she's
going to be calling them.

514
00:30:08.206 --> 00:30:10.072
That look usually
gets us in trouble.

515
00:30:10.342 --> 00:30:12.834
Well. she might not be
getting in touch with them.

516
00:30:12.911 --> 00:30:14.345
What if they got
in touch with her?

517
00:30:14.413 --> 00:30:17.042
Wu says Shellow's not
cooperating until he sees a lawyer.

518
00:30:17.115 --> 00:30:18.355
We don't need him to cooperate.

519
00:30:18.417 --> 00:30:21.785
We just need him to do what
he does best. send a message.

520
00:30:22.454 --> 00:30:24.582
And he doesn't know we're
protecting Adalind Schade.

521
00:30:24.823 --> 00:30:27.019
And neither does
Melissa Wincroft.

522
00:30:27.959 --> 00:30:29.393
Hey. Doug.

523
00:30:29.861 --> 00:30:32.092
How you doing? Are you hungry?

524
00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:35.398
<i>You and I have some
unfinished business.</i>

525
00:30:36.301 --> 00:30:39.499
So. why don't we pick
up where we left off?

526
00:30:42.874 --> 00:30:44.433
You were about to
show me some tweets.

527
00:30:47.412 --> 00:30:48.641
Tweet this.

528
00:30:48.714 --> 00:30:51.206
I don't have to do anything
until my lawyer gets here.

529
00:30:51.283 --> 00:30:52.546
Oh. Doug.

530
00:30:53.251 --> 00:30:54.731
we have you at the
scene of the crime.

531
00:30:55.153 --> 00:30:57.452
We tailed you to a meeting
with our prime suspect.

532
00:30:57.522 --> 00:30:59.582
You will do seven to
10 on conspiracy alone.

533
00:30:59.725 --> 00:31:01.250
no matter how
good your lawyer is.

534
00:31:01.893 --> 00:31:04.624
So. why do you want to keep
protecting Melissa Wincroft?

535
00:31:07.866 --> 00:31:09.994
There's going to be
another victim. isn't there?

536
00:31:12.104 --> 00:31:13.333
Tell me.

537
00:31:14.373 --> 00:31:15.705
Who is it?

538
00:31:17.142 --> 00:31:19.236
Doug. come on.
do yourself a favor.

539
00:31:19.311 --> 00:31:21.712
who is Melissa
Wincroft's next target?

540
00:31:22.114 --> 00:31:23.291
Nick. Captain needs to see you.

541
00:31:23.315 --> 00:31:24.955
Hank. I'm in the middle
of something. Now.

542
00:31:27.185 --> 00:31:28.813
This isn't over.

543
00:31:42.667 --> 00:31:44.499
Oscar worthy
performance. De Niro.

544
00:31:44.569 --> 00:31:45.730
Middle school drama club.

545
00:31:45.804 --> 00:31:46.863
This better work.

546
00:31:47.239 --> 00:31:49.299
It will. It's in his nature.

547
00:31:53.879 --> 00:31:55.745
Come on. Doug. the
phone's right there. buddy.

548
00:31:55.814 --> 00:31:56.907
Take the bait.

549
00:32:09.961 --> 00:32:11.759
There it is. Wu. On it.

550
00:32:11.830 --> 00:32:13.321
How quick does this stuff work?

551
00:32:13.398 --> 00:32:15.697
There. He just sent a direct
message to a blocked user.

552
00:32:15.934 --> 00:32:17.654
Well. can you... Of
course I can. I'm Asian.

553
00:32:19.271 --> 00:32:21.069
Okay. here's the message.

554
00:32:21.139 --> 00:32:22.539
"They don't know.

555
00:32:22.774 --> 00:32:24.037
"As open."

556
00:32:25.577 --> 00:32:26.909
"As open?"

557
00:32:27.479 --> 00:32:28.606
"As."

558
00:32:29.981 --> 00:32:31.813
A-S. Adalind Schade.

559
00:32:34.486 --> 00:32:36.478
He just told Melissa
Wincroft to make their move.

560
00:32:57.576 --> 00:32:59.704
You're home early. Miss Schade.

561
00:33:01.580 --> 00:33:03.105
She's headed your way.

562
00:33:15.026 --> 00:33:17.018
Which floor. Miss Schade?

563
00:33:21.466 --> 00:33:22.525
Bird's in the nest.

564
00:33:22.601 --> 00:33:23.728
Nice work.

565
00:33:23.802 --> 00:33:26.328
Now. let's hope Melissa
Wincroft takes the bait.

566
00:33:27.839 --> 00:33:29.467
Do you really
think this will work?

567
00:33:29.541 --> 00:33:31.701
We've got to smoke her out
of her hiding place somehow.

568
00:33:31.943 --> 00:33:33.878
Every eye in the
department is on your place.

569
00:33:34.246 --> 00:33:35.612
Thanks. detectives.

570
00:33:35.981 --> 00:33:38.382
This is probably a big
inconvenience for you.

571
00:33:39.084 --> 00:33:41.053
Well. we're just doing our jobs.

572
00:33:41.119 --> 00:33:42.246
Nothing more.

573
00:33:45.423 --> 00:33:47.358
Anyone want some room service?

574
00:33:48.293 --> 00:33:49.761
I'm not really hungry.

575
00:33:50.996 --> 00:33:52.726
No? How about some tea?

576
00:33:52.797 --> 00:33:56.165
Chamomile is nice and relaxing.

577
00:33:56.902 --> 00:33:57.902
Sure.

578
00:34:00.839 --> 00:34:03.172
Nature's full of
powerful concoctions.

579
00:34:07.312 --> 00:34:09.247
I'm going to make
yours a double.

580
00:34:10.015 --> 00:34:12.575
There's got to be a coffee
maker around here somewhere.

581
00:34:16.655 --> 00:34:18.123
I know what you are.

582
00:34:18.189 --> 00:34:19.189
I'm an attorney.

583
00:34:19.291 --> 00:34:20.350
You're a Hexenbiest.

584
00:34:20.692 --> 00:34:22.251
Just like Serena and Camilla.

585
00:34:22.460 --> 00:34:23.484
I saw their marks.

586
00:34:23.562 --> 00:34:25.030
Detective. I don't know...

587
00:34:25.096 --> 00:34:26.340
You tried to kill my
aunt in the hospital.

588
00:34:26.364 --> 00:34:27.730
but you got me instead.

589
00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:30.332
So. were they in on it with you?

590
00:34:31.603 --> 00:34:32.603
Your sisters?

591
00:34:34.072 --> 00:34:35.233
Who do you work for?

592
00:34:41.846 --> 00:34:42.939
Okay.

593
00:34:44.382 --> 00:34:46.180
So you want to play the victim?

594
00:34:48.119 --> 00:34:49.610
So. tell me.

595
00:34:50.622 --> 00:34:52.887
why do the Mellifers
want you dead?

596
00:34:53.491 --> 00:34:55.653
You're a detective.
Figure it out.

597
00:34:56.328 --> 00:34:57.990
I don't like this any
more than you do.

598
00:34:58.063 --> 00:35:00.259
but if it's my duty
to protect you.

599
00:35:00.332 --> 00:35:01.709
I damn well better
have a good reason

600
00:35:01.733 --> 00:35:03.998
or I might have a
bad day at work.

601
00:35:06.371 --> 00:35:08.567
You shouldn't have involved me.

602
00:35:08.640 --> 00:35:10.768
I'm clean. I have
nothing to do with this.

603
00:35:10.842 --> 00:35:13.243
You have just as
much to lose as we do.

604
00:35:13.378 --> 00:35:15.108
I don't want to go to jail.

605
00:35:16.881 --> 00:35:18.315
How can someone like you

606
00:35:18.383 --> 00:35:20.215
take care of someone like us?

607
00:35:24.990 --> 00:35:26.356
They're going to find you.

608
00:35:28.193 --> 00:35:29.752
Not before I get to her.

609
00:35:29.828 --> 00:35:31.988
There's no guarantee he'll
understand what you've done.

610
00:35:32.063 --> 00:35:33.759
When she's dead.

611
00:35:34.833 --> 00:35:36.131
he'll understand.

612
00:35:37.636 --> 00:35:39.867
Let's just get this over with.

613
00:35:43.208 --> 00:35:44.540
They'll find her.

614
00:36:14.139 --> 00:36:15.266
Come on!

615
00:36:15.473 --> 00:36:17.499
I can't help you
unless you tell me

616
00:36:17.575 --> 00:36:19.373
why Melissa Wincroft
wants to kill you.

617
00:36:19.978 --> 00:36:23.210
You have no idea what
you're in the middle of.

618
00:36:23.548 --> 00:36:26.143
Huh. well. then who could
blame me for making a mistake

619
00:36:26.217 --> 00:36:28.550
and letting a queen Mellifer
kill another Hexenbiest.

620
00:36:32.991 --> 00:36:34.459
This won't end well.

621
00:36:34.993 --> 00:36:36.017
For you.

622
00:36:36.227 --> 00:36:37.422
Or you.

623
00:36:38.797 --> 00:36:39.890
If something happens to me.

624
00:36:39.964 --> 00:36:42.900
it won't just be a Grimm
killing a Hexenbiest.

625
00:36:43.535 --> 00:36:44.935
it'll be a cop

626
00:36:45.136 --> 00:36:48.595
who's let an innocent
woman die on his watch.

627
00:36:50.508 --> 00:36:52.101
Up to you.

628
00:36:53.411 --> 00:36:55.607
I gotta get a
little help in here!

629
00:37:05.123 --> 00:37:06.250
It won't budge!

630
00:37:14.499 --> 00:37:16.229
It's like they're
coming after us!

631
00:37:24.409 --> 00:37:25.604
Where are they going?

632
00:37:28.346 --> 00:37:29.439
Adalind!

633
00:37:30.915 --> 00:37:32.247
Adalind!

634
00:37:42.994 --> 00:37:45.054
No sign of forced entry!

635
00:37:45.463 --> 00:37:46.692
Why would she run?

636
00:37:46.765 --> 00:37:48.275
Button's still lit.
She didn't take it.

637
00:37:48.299 --> 00:37:49.597
I'm going up.

638
00:37:51.436 --> 00:37:52.665
Adalind!

639
00:38:11.256 --> 00:38:12.485
Adalind!

640
00:38:28.907 --> 00:38:30.170
Adalind!

641
00:38:37.816 --> 00:38:40.047
I have to kill her.
You don't understand.

642
00:38:40.251 --> 00:38:41.251
Drop it.

643
00:38:41.319 --> 00:38:42.429
I'm arresting you
for the murders

644
00:38:42.453 --> 00:38:44.012
of Serena Dunbrook
and Camilla Gotlieb.

645
00:38:44.088 --> 00:38:45.613
I did it to protect you.

646
00:38:45.757 --> 00:38:47.089
There's no excuse.

647
00:38:47.725 --> 00:38:49.990
We're clarions. We
send the warning call.

648
00:38:50.662 --> 00:38:51.857
We're on your side.

649
00:38:52.664 --> 00:38:53.927
The lawsuit.

650
00:38:53.998 --> 00:38:55.438
it was a conspiracy
to get rid of us.

651
00:38:55.466 --> 00:38:56.832
They're not just lawyers.

652
00:38:57.035 --> 00:38:58.799
It doesn't matter.
You killed two people.

653
00:38:58.870 --> 00:39:00.463
Two Hexenbiests.

654
00:39:00.772 --> 00:39:02.206
Closing the mill was their way

655
00:39:02.273 --> 00:39:03.969
of stopping us from warning you.

656
00:39:04.108 --> 00:39:05.132
Warning me?

657
00:39:05.977 --> 00:39:07.309
Something's coming.

658
00:39:07.478 --> 00:39:08.844
Something bad.

659
00:39:09.547 --> 00:39:11.413
I have to finish this.

660
00:39:12.083 --> 00:39:13.745
Melissa. don't!

661
00:39:16.955 --> 00:39:18.423
Melissa!

662
00:39:40.178 --> 00:39:42.807
This isn't your problem.
Don't make a mistake.

663
00:39:42.881 --> 00:39:44.321
She'll harm you.
Don't listen to her!

664
00:39:44.349 --> 00:39:46.409
Do your job.

665
00:39:46.484 --> 00:39:48.009
Melissa! You're a Grimm.

666
00:39:48.086 --> 00:39:49.520
That's more important.

667
00:40:00.732 --> 00:40:02.428
Help me. please!

668
00:40:02.767 --> 00:40:04.668
She killed my friends!

669
00:40:04.736 --> 00:40:05.736
Melissa. back away!

670
00:40:05.970 --> 00:40:07.529
Oh. no!

671
00:40:10.742 --> 00:40:12.904
Adalind. you okay?

672
00:40:21.386 --> 00:40:22.911
He's coming for you.

673
00:40:23.888 --> 00:40:24.888
Who?

674
00:40:25.556 --> 00:40:26.683
Beware.

675
00:40:27.592 --> 00:40:29.117
It's close.

676
00:41:01.526 --> 00:41:03.961
You have to hunt
down the bad ones.

677
00:41:04.595 --> 00:41:06.188
Just like your ancestors did.

678
00:41:18.343 --> 00:41:20.244
Hank said you
did the right thing.

679
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:23.505
Sometimes it's not that simple.

680
00:41:25.650 --> 00:41:27.949
If it was simple. they
wouldn't need you.

681
00:41:29.053 --> 00:41:30.783
I don't think I made
any difference.

682
00:41:31.789 --> 00:41:33.451
I tried to stop it.

683
00:41:34.425 --> 00:41:35.893
but I didn't.

684
00:41:37.729 --> 00:41:40.255
I think you made a pretty
big difference to Hank

685
00:41:40.331 --> 00:41:42.163
and the woman
whose life you saved.

686
00:41:45.303 --> 00:41:48.171
Doesn't that make you feel a little
bit better about what happened?

687
00:41:52.610 --> 00:41:54.101
Yeah. it does.

688
00:42:01.586 --> 00:42:02.952
I'm cold.

689
00:42:04.222 --> 00:42:05.588
I need to close the window.

690
00:42:05.656 --> 00:42:07.147
No. I got it. Okay.

691
00:42:07.225 --> 00:42:08.750
Go back to bed.

692
00:42:32.517 --> 00:42:33.712
What happened?

693
00:42:34.252 --> 00:42:35.880
I just got stung.

693
00:42:36.305 --> 00:43:36.437
